[start section id="$final"]
Final Diagnosis
Colon, right hemicolectomy:  Invasive grade 4 (of 4) adenocarcinoma forming an ulcerated mass (5.4 x 5.2 x 1.8 cm) located in the cecum.  The tumor invades through the muscularis propria into pericolic fat.  The proximal ileal and distal colon margins are grossly uninvolved.  Multiple (18) regional lymph nodes are negative for tumor.

With available surgical materials, [AJCC pT3N0](7th edition, 2010).



[end section id="$final"]
[start section id="$gross"]

Gross Description
A.  Received fresh labeled right colon is a right hemicolectomy specimen consisting of 17.0 cm of terminal ileum, 18.0 cm of colon, with no appendix. A 5.4 x 5.2 x 1.8 cm ulcerative mass is present within the cecum, 2.0 cm from the ileocecal valve. Grossly, the mass extends to the pericolonic fat.  The mass is 18.0 cm from the distal mucosal margin. Multiple lymph nodes are identified within the mesenteric fat.  Representative sections are submitted. Grossed by MORAN





[end section id="$gross"]